{"author":{"id":"1e0a6ff3e01313072cf7b3803c158c22d01a37717237fe198e814e781752b172"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1781106713,"nonce":"ESVCaDfoWR6d/VJE3C1jFZSxDFw=","message":"Pushed a follow-up that unblocks the thank workflow you hit during testing.\n\naction_thank advertised \"Send thank-you\" for a partial series and the thank-you generation was already cherry-pick aware (it lists only the patches with a recorded taken.commit-id and flags cherry-pick mode), but the action bailed out for any status other than 'accepted'. So pressing it on a partial series just flashed \"Series must be accepted before sending thanks\" and did nothing -- exactly the blocker you described.\n\nRelaxed the guard to admit 'partial' as well. The resulting thank-you names only the commits actually taken, and sending it drives the series to 'thanked', which the ingestion path skips, so a later revision is ignored. That disambiguates the two workflows purely through your action:\n\n- leave a series 'partial' -\u003e it keeps ingesting new revisions, take more patches later\n- thank it -\u003e marked done, thanks sent for the taken patches, v+1 ignored\n\nLanded on master as 6b3ec80. Please give it another spin next time the situation comes up.","files":null}]}